	<h2>DIY Improvements to Existing Fences</h2>
	<p>If you already have a fence, consider these enhancements:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Seal all gaps with caulk or weatherstripping</li>
		<li>Add mass-loaded vinyl sheets behind boards</li>
		<li>Install second layer of boards</li>
		<li>Extend height with solid lattice</li>
		<li>Add dense landscaping</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Conclusion</h2>
	<p>While no fence provides complete soundproofing, the right design significantly reduces noise intrusion. Focus on mass, height, and eliminating gaps for best results. For Stockton homeowners dealing with traffic noise or commercial neighbors, a well-designed noise-reducing fence can transform your outdoor experience.</p>

	<p>Remember that noise reduction often works best as part of a comprehensive approach—combining fencing with landscaping, proper positioning, and sometimes white noise features for the most pleasant outdoor environment.</p>

	<p>Want to discuss noise reduction options for your property? Contact us for a consultation on the best solutions for your specific situation.</p>

